{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "NonPay API",
    "description": "NonPay Payment Processing API for collect (deposit) and disburse (withdrawal) operations\n\n## Webhook Callbacks and Signature Verification\n\nWhen payment status changes occur, NonPay sends HTTP POST requests to your configured callback URL with transaction details. All callbacks include an RSA-SHA256 signature for verification.\n\n### Signature Verification\n\nEvery callback includes a `signature` header containing an RSA-SHA256 signature (base64-encoded) of the JSON request body. Verify this signature using the public RSA key provided in your API credentials panel.\n\n**Node.js verification example:**\n```javascript\nimport { createPublicKey, verify } from 'node:crypto';\n\nasync function verifyCallback(body, headers) {\n  const bodyString = JSON.stringify(body);\n  const signatureHeader = headers['signature'];\n  \n  const publicKey = createPublicKey({\n    key: YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY_FROM_PANEL,\n    format: 'pem'\n  });\n  \n  return verify(\n    'SHA256',\n    Buffer.from(bodyString),\n    publicKey,\n    Buffer.from(signatureHeader, 'base64')\n  );\n}\n```\n\n**Python verification example:**\n```python\nfrom cryptography.hazmat.primitives import hashes, serialization\nfrom cryptography.hazmat.primitives.asymmetric import padding\nimport base64\nimport json\n\ndef verify_callback(body, signature_header):\n    body_string = json.dumps(body, separators=(',', ':'), sort_keys=True)\n    signature_bytes = base64.b64decode(signature_header)\n    \n    public_key = serialization.load_pem_public_key(\n        YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY_FROM_PANEL.encode()\n    )\n    \n    public_key.verify(\n        signature_bytes,\n        body_string.encode(),\n        padding.PKCS1v15(),\n        hashes.SHA256()\n    )\n    return True\n```\n\n**PHP verification example:**\n```php\nfunction verifyCallback($body, $signatureHeader) {\n    $bodyString = json_encode($body, JSON_UNESCAPED_SLASHES | JSON_SORT_KEYS);\n    $signature = base64_decode($signatureHeader);\n    \n    $publicKey = openssl_pkey_get_public(YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY_FROM_PANEL);\n    \n    return openssl_verify(\n        $bodyString,\n        $signature,\n        $publicKey,\n        OPENSSL_ALGO_SHA256\n    ) === 1;\n}\n```\n\n### Callback Response Handling\n\n- **HTTP 200/201**: Payment status change is confirmed and applied\n- **HTTP 405 (Method Not Allowed)**: Decline the status change (only valid for reversals and adjustments)\n- **Other 4xx/5xx**: Indicates delivery error; NonPay will retry for up to 24 hours\n\nAlways respond with correct HTTP status codes. Avoid other error responses during normal operation, as they trigger automatic retry mechanisms.\n\n### Callback Delivery and Retry\n\nCallbacks are delivered with exponential backoff retry logic over 24 hours. If your endpoint does not confirm receipt (200/201), the system will continue retrying. For status changes that require merchant confirmation (adjustments, reversals), responding with 405 reverts the transaction to its previous state.",
    "version": "2.2.1"
  },
